The paper deals with clustering algorithms and their optimization for large datasets, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The use of k-means clustering also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AR). The use of a multi-core hardware-software co-design architecture also suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
